* She glared at Prowl as he hobbled around the corner, but the pain in her 
shoulder was beginning to flare.
However, as the same as her mast merged transformation, pain brought back 
the logic side of her mind, and what agression she was feeling before was 
beginning to dampen.

Her look towards Prowl sofened a bit, and for the first time since she had 
transformed, she stepped towards him with no intention to attack.
It troubled her that she had hurt him, and she knew that it was her fault he 
was like this too.
It was barely able to be heard...but she sighed.

With a heave of her body she slowly began to walk towards him, but leaning 
heavily on her good side. Her logic had not completely returned to realize 
just what had happened to her yet, but she knew that Prowl wasn't out to get 
her and was more concerned about her then himself.
There was a large lump on her shoulder, where the synthetic bone now stuck 
out.

She stopped les then a meter away from Prowl and simply bowed her head, a 
tired expression on her face. She was hurt, tired and confused.*
